The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The problem of facility location on a metric induced by a publicly known tree involves designing algorithms to solve a computational problem (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the optimization of utility, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of incentives and the analysis of competitive ratios are techniques commonly used in algorithmic game theory (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with information theory, specifically the problem of agents with private information, which falls under the subfield of information theory (cs.IT).
